Hello everyone. I could use some guidance with the import api. I'm attempting to perform an import where I am updating contact objects and associating them with either new or pre-existing companies... When I create an import I get a successful response, but upon a get request on the import id I see that the rows are not imported.
`"metadata": {`
    `"objectLists": [],`
    `"counters": {`
      `"TOTAL_ROWS": 7,`
      `"PROPERTY_VALUES_EMITTED": 7,`
      `"ERRORS": 7,`
      `"MAPPED_COLUMNS": 6`
    `},`

API Call:
```  const url = "<https://api.HubSpot.com/crm/v3/imports>";
  const token = HubSpotKey;
  const form = new FormData();

  form.append(
    "importRequest",
    JSON.stringify({
      name: "contacts import",
      files: [
        {
          fileName: path.basename(filePath),
          fileFormat: "CSV",
          dateFormat: "YEAR_MONTH_DAY",
          marketableContactImport: false,
          fileImportPage: {
            hasHeader: true,
            columnMappings: columns,
          },
        },
      ],
    })
  );
  form.append("files", fs.createReadStream(filePath));

  try {
    const response = await axios.post(url, form, {
      headers: {
        ...form.getHeaders(),
        Accept: "application/json",
        Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
      },
    });

    console.log(response.data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error in POST request:", error);
  }```
I have made sure that my columns mappings are correct.
